race.description: Queanbeyan Cup 28 Nov Country Boosted Mdn Plate
race.comment: Nick Olive-trained TIS NO MAN (5) resumed here and looked a run short. He draws inside today and the longer sprint is sure to suit. He will get every chance in a winnable assignment. BASTION (8) has been well supported in his last two starts but disappointed. Has some notable gear changes today and the Boudvillain-Seib linkage is potent. Clearly has ability and from a low barrier will get every chance to turn things around. CASINO SHAW (10) improved again finding one better over 1200m at the Sapphire Coast. Has an awkward barrier but can run into the finish again. KERMANDO (1) returns from a spell. Placed in a recent trial. Opened last campaign with a sixth at Sapphire Coast over 1400m. Keep safe. Something for the Multiples: STARS AND SPANGLES (4)
